tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
Soo many doctors and soo many options specifically in the pandemic i was lucky to have searched for and found Dr.Tharanth in practo. 
In just three days i consulted him for myself, dad and my wife with fever and other symptoms. And he is one of those doctors who does not over prescribe medicines. 
He explains everything in detail and a clear communicator.It is very rare now a days to find such knowledgeable and down to earth personalities in his line of profession.

And we are lucky and glad that we got to know him and recovering fast.
Will remember him forever and will confidently recommend other when in need.

Once again Thank you Dr.Tharanth.
reply_text:
Thankyou sir for your valuable feedback.
Thankyou for taking your time out to write such a detailed feedback.

review: 15min is not enough. Video did not work  and consumed my  time out of 15min. Time is very short to explain Dr. And Dr is is hurry to attain other appointments
reply_text:
Dear Sir,
Thankyou for the feedback. 15 minutes is adequate time to discuss one's ailments. I texted you 2 minutes before the actual appointment time and the video call was not answered for the next 8 minutes when I had to initiate the audio call. Hence I understand there was less time but I thought you still narrated the entire clinical history. I have also brought it to the notice of practo support team regarding the technical issues of the video call not going through. Apologies for the same.
Also the consultation is giving you free chat messages for the next 7 days where you can ask any doubts or queries to the doctor and it's not just one point consultation. 
I hope your daughter has recovered well by now. Thankyou for your valuable feedback.
